<sect1 id="dir_421e32f00e1d9f04a50f71a0b4750541_1autotoc_md126">
<title>helios::engine::mechanics::spawn::manager</title><para>Managers for spawn and despawn request processing.</para>
<para>This namespace contains the SpawnManager which handles the actual spawning and despawning of GameObjects from pools.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_421e32f00e1d9f04a50f71a0b4750541_1autotoc_md127">
<title>Managers</title><para><table rows="2" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Manager  </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Purpose  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>SpawnManager</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Processes spawn/despawn requests, manages pool lifecycle  </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_421e32f00e1d9f04a50f71a0b4750541_1autotoc_md128">
<title>Responsibilities</title><para>The SpawnManager:</para>
<para>1. Receives SpawnRequest and DespawnRequest instances 2. Queues requests for deferred processing 3. During flush: processes despawns first, then spawns 4. Uses GameObjectFactory to populate pools 5. Registers as PoolRequestHandler for its assigned pool</para>
</sect1>
